properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover for Richard Archbold Trans-Pacific Flight / New Guinea Expedition and Return, May 24, 1938 - July 1, 1939; accompanied by map, newspaper clipping, and supplemental information from donor (b-e).a. Envelope with dark brown rectangular cachet with ten lines of text at bottom left corner, "Richard Archbold Trans-Pacific Flight" at top with stops indicated; three postmarks (from left to right): "Hollandia 11.5.39.10-IIV" (May 11, 1939), June 3, 1939, Rose Bay East 39 NSW Aust, and New York, N.Y. May 24, 1938; orange 6-cent stamp, brown 5-shilling stamp, and red 2-cent stamp; backstamped June 12, 1939, C. & W. Ltd., Cocos; addressed to: The American Museum of Natural History, Central Park West at 79th Street, New York, N. Y.; signed by Richard Archbold.b. route map: photocopied map with text at bottom left corner Archbold New Guinea Expedition Flying Boat "GUBA" PBY-2; folds out to approx. 24 x 11 inches; single-sided, irregularly folded.c. newspaper clipping: small item circled in pencil regarding the auction of a 1938 Richard Archbold Trans-Pacific Flight and Expedition to New Guinea cover.d. magazine clipping: item on Richard Archbold and Transpacific Flight Expedition.e. information sheet: photocopied information on 8.5 x 3 inch sheet regarding Archbold's San Diego-New Guinea flight on June 2-9 1938.
properties.wof:name: airmail flight cover: Richard Archbold Trans-Pacific Flight / New Guinea Expedition and Return, May 24, 1938 - July 1, 1939
